This paper deals with social choice theory, which is a subfield of game theory. The paper specifically focuses on dominant strategy implementation in private values settings, which falls under the category of mechanism design. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from aggregation literature, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with utility maximization, which is a common topic in cs.EC (Economics and Computation) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
